"title": "7024: church, nature and foundations of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7024: church, nature and foundations of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The church is the people called by God, who are united by their faith in Christ and by their common life in him. Various descriptions and metaphors emphasise the continuity between the people of God in the OT and NT.</p>\n<h2>NT images of the church</h2>\n<h3>The body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:5\">ROM 12:4–12:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:6\">EPH 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:24\">COL 1:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:19\">COL 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:15\">COL 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>God's building or temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16-1Cor3:17\">1CO 3:16–3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10\">1CO 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:21-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:21–2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:6\">HEB 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:21\">HEB 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>A plant or vine</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1-John15:8\">JHN 15:1–15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:17-Rom11:24\">ROM 11:17–11:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:6-1Cor3:8\">1CO 3:6–3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:14-John10:16\">JHN 10:14–10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:33\">MAT 25:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32\">LUK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28-Acts20:29\">ACT 20:28–20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:2–5:4</a></p>\n<h3>The bride of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31-Eph5:32\">EPH 5:31–5:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7\">REV 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:17\">REV 22:17</a></p>\n<h3>God's household or family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19\">EPH 2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:35-John8:36\">JHN 8:35–8:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:15\">EPH 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:15\">1TI 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:11\">HEB 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:17\">1PE 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>NT descriptions of the church</h2>\n<h3>Emphasising continuity with the OT church</h3>\n<p>Abraham's offspring:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:16\">ROM 4:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:7\">GAL 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:25\">ROM 9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9-1Pet2:10\">1PE 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:26\">GAL 4:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22\">HEB 12:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:9-Rev21:10\">REV 21:9–21:10</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:16\">GAL 6:16</a> <em>the Israel of God</em></p>\n<h3>Emphasising God's call and authority in the church</h3>\n<p>Sons of God:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:9\">MAT 5:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15-Rom8:16\">ROM 8:15–8:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26\">GAL 3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:5-Gal4:6\">GAL 4:5–4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:10\">1JN 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:22\">MAT 24:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:7\">ROM 11:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:10\">2TI 2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1\">1PE 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:7\">GAL 4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:7\">TIT 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:14\">HEB 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:17\">HEB 6:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:4\">1PE 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:6\">REV 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:10\">REV 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:6\">REV 20:6</a></p>\n<h3>Descriptions applied to the church by outsiders</h3>\n<p>Followers of the Way:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:2\">ACT 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:9\">ACT 19:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:23\">ACT 19:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:4\">ACT 22:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:14\">ACT 24:14</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:26\">ACT 11:26</a> <em>Christians</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:5\">ACT 24:5</a> <em>“the Nazarene sect” means people belonging to Jesus the “Nazarene” (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:23\">Mt 2:23</a>)</em></p>\n<h3>Descriptions used by Christians</h3>\n<p>The believers. All these titles are seldom in the singular, emphasising the corporateness of Christian life:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:15\">ACT 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:44\">ACT 2:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:12\">ACT 5:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:12\">1TI 4:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1-Acts6:2\">ACT 6:1–6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:19\">ACT 9:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:26\">ACT 11:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:22\">ACT 14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:1\">ACT 20:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:7\">ROM 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:25\">ROM 15:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:1\">1CO 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:33\">1CO 14:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:1\">EPH 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:21\">PHP 4:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:12\">COL 1:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3\">JUD 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Other NT descriptions of the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:15\">1TI 3:15</a> <em>the pillar and foundation of the truth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:23\">HEB 12:23</a> <em>The church of the firstborn. “the firstborn” is plural, referring to Christians as those born again through their union with Christ, who is the firstborn.</em></p>\n<h2>The foundation of the church</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as the church's foundation-stone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:11\">1CO 3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:24-Matt7:25\">MAT 7:24–7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:42\">MAT 21:42</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:10\">MRK 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:17\">LUK 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:11\">ACT 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:20\">EPH 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:6\">1PE 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:16\">ISA 28:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:7\">1PE 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:22\">PSA 118:22</a></p>\n<h3>Apostles and prophets as founders of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:20\">EPH 2:19–2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:18-Matt16:19\">MAT 16:18–16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:14\">REV 21:14</a></p>\n<h2>The church as God's people</h2>\n<h3>A people chosen by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:33\">ROM 8:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:5\">JAS 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>A people called by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:6\">ROM 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:39\">ACT 2:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:2\">1CO 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:9\">1CO 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:6\">GAL 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:14\">2TH 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:1\">JUD 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>A people loved by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:10\">1PE 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:1–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:4-Titus3:7\">TIT 3:4–3:7</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:8-Heb8:10\">HEB 8:8–8:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:27\">ROM 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:20-Isa59:21\">ISA 59:20–59:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:16\">HEB 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:31-Jer31:33\">JER 31:31–31:33</a></p>",
